    "narrative": "The Austin Waves lineup is anchored today by **Kyle Tucker**, who secures an elite 85.90 rating against Feltner. With a massive +14% park factor and favorable SP dynamics, **Kyle Tucker** is our primary source of upside. **Gunnar Henderson** follows closely with an 81.76 score, benefiting from a +14% platoon edge against G. Williams; however, we must monitor the 31% rain risk, which could shorten his day. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** also projects strongly (73.66) as he exploits a favorable matchup against Houser, utilizing both a solid platoon split and an elevated order position that maximizes his scoring potential.\n\nThe most difficult decision for the daily optimizer involved **Nasim Nunez** (57.94), who fell just shy of the threshold to displace our lower-ranked starters. While **Nasim Nunez** offers high-end speed potential, his projected efficiency was marginally suppressed by a 1.86s catcher pop-time and a lower-order placement, leading us to favor the power upside of **Josh Lowe** (71.68) and **Andy Pages** (72.64). Both **Josh Lowe** and **Andy Pages** benefit significantly from a slow opposing pitcher delivery, which provides a unique edge in our pursuit of stolen bases.\n\nWe are exercising caution with **Jackson Merrill** (55.67), whose score is tempered by a negative platoon shift against Yusei Kikuchi and a challenging catcher matchup. Conversely, **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (64.56) and **Miguel Vargas** (64.64) are solid starts despite tough opposing arms, as they maintain strong underlying metrics. We are currently holding **Drake Baldwin** (48.10) in the lineup, though his output against Cristopher S\u00e1nchez remains a point of concern; we are prepared to pivot if the final lineups signal a shift in his availability or expected production.",
